            <h2>Basic Information About Blood</h2>
            <p><strong>What is Blood?</strong> Blood is a fluid in our body that delivers essential substances like oxygen, nutrients, and hormones to cells and removes waste products.</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Red Blood Cells (RBCs):</strong> Carry oxygen from the lungs to the rest of the body.</li>
                <li><strong>White Blood Cells (WBCs):</strong> Help fight infections.</li>
                <li><strong>Platelets:</strong> Aid in blood clotting to stop bleeding.</li>
                <li><strong>Plasma:</strong> A yellowish liquid that carries proteins, hormones, and waste.</li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>Blood Types:</strong> There are four main blood groups—A, B, AB, and O—each with a positive or negative Rh factor.</p>
            <p><strong>Importance of Blood Donation:</strong> Blood donations are critical for surgeries, trauma care, and cancer treatment.</p>
        </div>
