                <p>Most healthy individuals aged 18-65, weighing at least 50 kg, can donate. Eligibility may vary by country.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-card">
                <h3>How often can I donate blood?</h3>
                <p>Whole blood can be donated every 8 weeks. Plasma and platelet donation intervals may differ, with plasma donations allowed every 2 weeks in some places.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-card">
                <h3>Can I donate if I have recently traveled?</h3>
                <p>Travel to certain regions or recent vaccinations may require a waiting period. Check with the donation center for specific deferrals.</p>
            </div>
